verses.roman:
ei-mate raghunātha āilā nīlācale
prabhura caraṇe yāñā mililā kutūhale

synonyms: ei-mate—in this way; raghunātha—Raghunātha Bhaṭṭa; āilā—came; nīlācale—to Jagannātha Purī; prabhura caraṇe—to the lotus feet of Śrī Caitanya Mahāprabhu; yāñā—going; mililā—met; kutūhale—in great delight.
translation: Traveling in this way, Raghunātha Bhaṭṭa soon arrived at Jagannātha Purī. There, with great delight, he met Śrī Caitanya Mahāprabhu and fell at His lotus feet.
